TRUSTABLE-SOFTWARE: This
release of JSON-Library
also referred in the
documentation as nlohmann/json
library is Trustable.

TT-EXPECTATIONS: Documentation
is provided within eclipse-score/inc_nlohmann_json,
specifying what the nlohmann/json
library is expected to
do, and what it must
not do, and how this
is verified.

WFJ-03: The service provided
by the nlohmann/json
library checks the well-formedness
of numbers.

NJF-08: The service provided
by the nlohmann/json
library accepts numbers
according to RFC8259
ยง6.

NJF-08.1: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does accept integers
within the limits of
64-bit double.

NJF-08.2: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does accept integers
according to IEEE 754
binary64.

NJF-08.3: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does not accept
NaN and infinity.

NJF-08.4: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does accept e
or E for numbers with
exponent within the bounds
of double.

NJF-08.5: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does not accept
u0415 and u0436 (cyrillic
e and E) as exponent
signs in numbers with
exponent.

NJF-08.6: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does not accept
invalid syntax for numbers.

NJF-08.7: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does accept decimal
points in numbers within
the bounds of double.

NJF-08.8: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does not accept
leading zeroes.

NJF-08.9: The service
provided by the nlohmann/json
library does not accept
any other digit symbol
than 0-9.

TA-BEHAVIOURS: Expected
or required behaviours
for the nlohmann/json
library are identified,
specified, verified and
validated based on analysis.
